{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_dusk_poem/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Our fatigue subtly sets in,<br>\nRest and all of her charms beckon,<br>\nDarkness is destined to ascend,<br>\nThe light bringer will come again,<br>\nDay almost played out to her end,<br>\nBeaten down by the hour hand,<br>\nBeauty's shadowed with all darkened,<br>\nThe curtain's called across the land,<br>\nAn encore is not to be played,<br>\nLeft with the darkness we've to brave,<br>\nAs it was, just hidden by change,<br>\nNo longer do scenes look the same,<br>\nMy pleasant green land turned away,<br>\nThe shame of such beauty in shade,<br>\nFacing west with goodbyes to say,<br>\nNever to be caught running late.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 03, 2020","title":"Dusk","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/6da84d7b856952a451bbffb776c3f901/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 03 Dusk.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/cee33449bce465b3032b9e25b0eb1915/7d509/nature_poem_dusk.jpg","srcSet":"/static/cee33449bce465b3032b9e25b0eb1915/f836f/nature_poem_dusk.jpg 200w,\n/static/cee33449bce465b3032b9e25b0eb1915/2244e/nature_poem_dusk.jpg 400w,\n/static/cee33449bce465b3032b9e25b0eb1915/7d509/nature_poem_dusk.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_dusk_poem/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}